news.title: Delhi: DDA launches phase-II for 5,382 in situ flats in Kalkaji slums
news.para: DDA had taken up in situ slum redevelopment of three clusters in Kalkaji Extension — Bhoomiheen Camp, Navjeevan Camp and Jawaharlal Nehru Camp.

news.title: Maharashtra: MMR notification for societies comes under flak
news.para: The move has come under flak. As per rules, administrators cannot take policy decisions such as redevelopment and major refurbishments except for day-to-day maintenance.

news.title: Gurugram: FIRs against 12 in DLF-3 for illegal construction
news.para: The DTCP has recommended FIRs against 50 property owners of three blocks — S, U and V — of DLF-3 for allegedly carrying out unauthorised construction in violation of the building code.

news.title: Housing demand up 6.7% in Q1, supply remains stable: Magicbricks Report
news.para: Mumbai with 15.2% rise, Gurugram 9.6%, Noida 8.2% and Delhi 5.6% witnessed highest sequential growth in demand, while Greater Noida with 6%, Mumbai 3.8%, Ahmedabad 3.2%, and Chennai 2.9% exhibited maximum growth in supply.

news.title: Mumbai: HDIL promoter gets bail in money laundering case
news.para: ​It is alleged that HDIL promoters Rakesh Wadhawan and his son Sarang, along with others, conspired to cheat PMC Bank with the help of its former office bearers. Sarang will remain in jail as he is accused in other cases.

news.title: Consumer courts empowered to direct refund, compensate buyer for not delivering flat: SC
news.para: The apex court said that it is clear from the statutory position that the Commission is empowered to direct refund of the price or the charges paid by the consumer.

news.title: Delhi-NCR sees over 2.5 fold jump in office leasing during Jan-Mar: Report
news.para: Office leasing stood at 7,00,000 square feet in the January-March period of last year. The new supply of office space fell 10 per cent to 1 million square feet from 1.1 million square feet. The Delhi-NCR has a total stock of office space of 118.7 million square feet at the end of the last month.

news.title: Rainwater harvesting must for all Indore buildings, new and old
news.para: The new rules came into effect after the Madhya Pradesh government on April 4 notified Indore Municipal Corporation (Rainwater Harvesting) Bylaws, 2022.

news.title: Godrej Properties inks pact to develop 7-lakh-sq-ft residential project in Mumbai
news.para: This project is an extension of Godrej Tranquil and Godrej Nest and will offer around 7 lakh sq ft of saleable area. To be developed as a modern residential project comprising of apartments of various configurations, it is estimated to have booking value potential of around Rs 1,000 crore.

news.title: Kochi: Rehabilitation package for GIFT City gets approval
news.para: According to the package, an amount of Rs 1.38 crore would be distributed to 98 persons, including 24 families, whose land and houses that would be acquired for the project.

news.title: Emaar India's director Hadi Badri resigns
news.para: “Due to my pre-occupation with other engagements, I am not in a position to devote my time to the affairs of the Company as a Director. Accordingly, I am submitting my resignation as director of the company with immediate effect,” Badri said in his resignation letter.

news.title: Walton Street BlackSoil debt fund invests Rs 75 crore in Shapoorji Pallonji's JV
news.para: The joint entity is developing a residential project in Mumbai’s Bandra (east) locality and the funds infused by WSBREDF-II will be utilized to complete the project.

news.title: Kanpur: KDA realizes Rs 2.62 crore compounding amount from Pragati Structures
news.para: It was a compounding amount which KDA had demanded last year but the builder company did not deposit the compounding amount and instead continued the construction work at the site.

news.title: Another private firm may be hired by Gurugram civic body for C&D waste collection
news.para: According to the MCG, an agreement between the corporation and a private company for collecting and transporting the C&D waste is currently on hold as the latter faces an inquiry for alleged fraud that it has denied.

news.title: Realtors in Rajasthan to get fee rebate to build homes for elders
news.para: Developers who will come forward to take these ‘retirement home’ scheme project will receive 100 per cent rebate in building plan fee, betterment levy and conversion charges.
